---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<MainLayout description="Truotek is a software development consultancy for teams that need sharp thinking, pragmatic engineering, and disciplined delivery.">
  <div class="page-shell">
    <div class="ambient ambient-left"></div>
    <div class="ambient ambient-right"></div>

    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="brand" href="/">Truotek</a>
      <nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="#services">Services</a>
        <a href="#approach">Approach</a>
        <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero section">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Software development consultancy</p>
          <h1>Build the right thing. Then ship it with discipline.</h1>
          <p class="hero-text">
            Truotek helps companies turn ambiguous software challenges into clear
            plans, stronger systems, and working products delivered with control.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button button-primary" href="#contact">Start a conversation</a>
            <a class="button button-secondary" href="#approach">See the approach</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="hero-panel">
          <p class="panel-kicker">Current focus</p>
          <ul class="signal-list">
            <li>New product prototypes and MVPs</li>
            <li>Internal tools that remove repetitive work</li>
            <li>Codebase cleanup before the next growth phase</li>
            <li>Fractional engineering support for small teams</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </section>

      <section class="section story-grid" id="services">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label">What Truotek can do</p>
          <h2>Clear enough for strategy. Practical enough for delivery.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="card-grid">
          <article class="feature-card">
            <p class="feature-number">01</p>
            <h3>Product engineering</h3>
            <p>
              From early validation to production-ready features, with scope,
              tradeoffs, and delivery kept visible throughout the process.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <p class="feature-number">02</p>
            <h3>Technical problem solving</h3>
            <p>
              Untangling brittle systems, isolating bottlenecks, and creating
              simpler paths forward when complexity starts slowing a team down.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <p class="feature-number">03</p>
            <h3>Delivery support</h3>
            <p>
              Helping teams scope work realistically, reduce implementation risk,
              and maintain momentum when priorities shift.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section approach-grid" id="approach">
        <div class="approach-copy">
          <p class="section-label">Approach</p>
          <h2>Pragmatic consulting for teams that need clarity, not theater.</h2>
          <p>
            Truotek works in short loops, communicates directly, and favors
            solutions that match the real business constraint. The goal is to
            reduce ambiguity, avoid unnecessary complexity, and deliver outcomes
            that hold up after launch.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="approach-steps">
          <article class="step-card">
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Find the real problem</h3>
            <p>
              Separate symptoms from root causes so effort goes toward the work
              that materially changes the outcome.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step-card">
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Choose an efficient path</h3>
            <p>
              Align scope, risk, and timeline before implementation starts to drift.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step-card">
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Ship something real</h3>
            <p>
              Deliver working software, concrete recommendations, or both. No
              vague handoff disconnected from execution.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section focus-band">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label">Engagements</p>
          <h2>Well suited for startups, small businesses, and teams in transition.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="focus-points">
          <p>Short advisory sprint</p>
          <p>Hands-on build support</p>
          <p>Architecture reset</p>
          <p>Fractional engineering capacity</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section contact-card" id="contact">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label">Contact</p>
          <h2>Have a software problem worth solving?</h2>
          <p>
            Truotek works with teams that need sharp technical judgment, reliable
            execution, and a practical path from problem to delivery.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-actions">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:hello@truotek.com">
            hello@truotek.com
          </a>
          <p class="contact-note">
            Email is the simplest place to start. A scheduling link can be added later.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <p>Truotek</p>
      <p>Software development consultancy</p>
      <p>&copy; {year}</p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
